1
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:52,960
You really don't remember me?

2
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,720
Wait!

3
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,160
Fun was my first love, you know.

4
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:59,240
Krit?

5
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,120
Yes.

6
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,200
Again?

7
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:03,800
I have a meeting tonight
with the client Krit set up.

8
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,360
If you join my team,

9
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,960
I guarantee you'll earn a lot.

10
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:13,400
Krit actually said that to you?

11
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:18,520
I don't know if he was serious or joking.

12
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:23,040
I don't think he's a good person.

13
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:29,360
Fun, the project you're doing with him
is almost done, right?

14
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,720
It wraps up in the middle of next month.

15
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,680
But…

16
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:41,160
I just took on a new project
with him yesterday.

17
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,000
Fun.

18
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:52,040
Can you not do it? I'm worried.

19
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,560
I don't want you
involved with him anymore.

20
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,800
I already accepted it.

21
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,320
We've even scheduled
a meeting with the client.

22
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:15,360
But don't worry.

23
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:18,480
I'll have Jess go with me.
I won't go alone.

24
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,560
Good.

25
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,920
I don't trust that guy at all.

26
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,080
Trust me, okay?

27
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:41,080
I'm always careful, and I never give him
a chance to get close.

28
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:46,120
I always trust you.

29
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,600
I never doubted you.

30
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:57,640
But still, be extra careful, okay?

31
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,400
Okay.

32
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,080
Hey!

33
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,480
Hey there, Auntie.

34
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,640
When did you get back?

35
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,520
Why didn't you tell me?

36
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:05,480
- Nueng!
- Hey there, Auntie-in-Law.

37
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,840
Nueng, I told you not to call me that.

38
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,960
We're the same age.
It makes me sound old, got it?

39
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:17,640
I'm just being respectful, Auntie Pafun.

40
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,800
That hurt.

41
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,760
That was too hard.

42
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:28,960
You always tease her. You're friends.

43
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,000
Oh.

44
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,080
Morning, Aunt Wee.

45
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,400
Morning. Morning.

46
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,400
- Morning.
- Good morning.

47
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:47,240
Oon, Fun, and…

48
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,760
This is Nubnueng,

49
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:53,080
my relative.
This is Aunt Chawee, our neighbor.

50
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,640
Hello, Aunt Chawee.

51
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,720
Hello.

52
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,360
Eh?

53
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,960
Are you staying for a few days?
I see two light green suitcases.

54
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:07,960
Aunt Wee, were you watering the plants?
I heard water running.

55
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,440
Oh, right, I…

56
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:15,000
The water! The Metropolitan Waterworks
is going to call me. I left it running.

57
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,520
I'll go take care of it first.

58
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:20,840
I'll go first. Don't call me.

59
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,400
- Come on, let's go inside.
- Let's go.

60
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,600
Oh, alright.

61
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,720
I think
that auntie next door is kinda weird.

62
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:40,920
Weird but nice. Don't mind her.

63
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,960
Yeah.

64
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:46,320
She's actually sweet.
Sometimes, she gets our packages

65
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,080
or waters our plants.

66
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,320
- Really?
- Yeah.

67
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,920
Does she live alone?

68
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,760
With her niece.

69
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:56,880
By the way, why didn't you tell us
you were coming back?

70
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,440
Hmm?

71
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,200
I made a quick decision.
I just came right away.

72
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:11,960
Nueng, be serious.
Is something wrong? You can tell us.

73
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:19,880
Well, I've decided
to move back to Thailand.

74
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,920
That's great. You can stay with us.

75
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,040
Yeah, we have plenty of rooms.

76
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:39,720
Well, we can talk about that later.

77
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:44,160
Right now,
we should celebrate your return.

78
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:46,800
Sure.

79
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:52,040
Wow, that's a lot.

80
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,200
Come on.

81
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,240
Looks so good.

82
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:59,200
I ordered a big meal for you.

83
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:02,920
Didn't know if you've had
spicy food like this over there.

84
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,880
This place is really good.

85
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,360
- Really?
- Yeah.

86
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,360
- Let's eat.
- Go ahead.

87
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,320
Extra fermented fish.

88
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,720
Let's go.

89
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,160
- Nueng.
- Bathroom.

90
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,720
- Bathroom! Bathroom!
- Right here.

91
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,640
Are you okay?

92
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,880
Thanks.

93
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,560
What's wrong with you?

94
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,640
Are you sick, Nueng?

95
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:59,080
Is that why you came back to Thailand?
For treatment?

96
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,440
Nueng, whatever it is,

97
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,280
we can take care of you, okay?

98
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,720
You two…

99
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,000
I'm not sick.

100
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,000
I'm just pregnant.

101
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:23,800
Pregnant?

102
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:34,600
Wait, did your boyfriend
come back with you?

103
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,559
I messed up.

104
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:45,240
At first, it was just a one-night stand
that almost turned into something more.

105
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,560
But then I found out…

106
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:57,320
he already has a wife and kids,
and I don't want to ruin anyone's family.

107
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:05,360
That's awful. He already has a family,
yet he still messed with you?

108
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,040
When I first found out I was pregnant,

109
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,120
I was confused.

110
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:17,800
But in the end,

111
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,000
I chose to keep the baby.

112
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:27,280
And I decided to move back to Thailand,
take design jobs here and there…

113
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:32,240
but right now, I guess I need
to figure out where to settle first.

114
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:35,640
And where are you supposed to settle?
Just stay here with us.

115
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:38,120
Yeah, just like old times.

116
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,440
Especially now that you're pregnant,
about to have a baby,

117
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:43,240
come live with us,
and we'll take care of you.

118
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:49,480
Would that really be okay?
How could I just move in as a third wheel?

119
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,280
Of course it would be okay.

120
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:55,120
I've always seen you as family,
never as anything else.

121
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,000
Yeah.

122
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,520
You are family.

123
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:04,040
I see you two as family too.

124
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:09,240
At first, I was thinking I'd come back,
buy a condo

125
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,680
and just live there as a mother and child.

126
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,560
Then go buy one.

127
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,880
We'll move in with you.

128
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,640
Yeah, do it.

129
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:22,200
Wait, what? Then how big a condo
would I have to buy?

130
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,360
Oh?

131
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,440
Exactly.

132
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,800
So just move in here with us.
Problem solved.

133
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,400
No need to buy anything.

134
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,800
Fine, fine.

135
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,400
I'll stay. But…

136
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:45,960
Are you staying or not?

137
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,240
Yes, yes. I'm staying.

138
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,520
That's all it took.

139
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:56,000
And have you told my mom yet?
About coming back to Thailand?

140
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:59,080
Of course I told her.
She's basically my godmother.

141
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:04,040
Ever since my parents died, Aunt Prang

142
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:06,320
has been
the only elder relative I have left.

143
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,040
She knows everything.

144
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:12,120
She knows all of it.
I just told her not to tell you two yet.

145
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,720
Tomorrow, I'm going back home to see her.

146
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:21,720
Then I'll drive you there myself.

147
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:25,320
No need. You just keep working.
She already booked me a van.

148
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,480
But you're pregnant.

149
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:31,160
Hey, I'm just pregnant.

150
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,480
I can still take care of myself.

151
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,640
I'm fine.

152
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:37,400
And then you're coming back here
to live with us.

153
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,440
KRIT (OLD FRIEND)

154
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,520
Yes, Krit?

155
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,440
Fun.

156
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:21,120
The client meeting this afternoon,
they want to move it to six. Are you free?

157
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,280
Six?

158
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:27,640
Yes, that works.

159
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,120
I'll send you the location.

160
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,000
What area is it?
I'll pick the place myself.

161
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:40,160
Fine. Around Srinakarin.

162
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,720
Srinakarin?

163
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,280
There's a new cafe around there,
near Suan Luang Rama IX.

164
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,880
The atmosphere is nice,
good for discussing work.

165
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,560
I'll send you the location.

166
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,040
See you this evening.

167
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:54,200
Alright.

168
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,440
Yes?

169
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,400
Oon-Oon.

170
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:11,720
I have a client meeting tonight at six.

171
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:16,000
The client isn't that Krit guy again,
is it?

172
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,120
It is.

173
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,040
Krit again.

174
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,360
I'll finish the meeting
and come right back, okay?

175
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,720
Okay.

176
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:32,400
Fun, when you get dressed,
video call me first, okay?

177
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,640
Why? You can just tell me now.

178
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:37,400
That's all for now. I'm driving.

179
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,920
Okay.

180
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,000
Yes, Oon?

181
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:06,800
Fun, can you put your phone down?

182
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,080
Hang up?

183
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:13,880
No, I mean put it on the dressing table.

184
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:16,240
Oh, okay.

185
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,520
PAFUN

186
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,240
Can you step back?

187
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,400
Step back?

188
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,120
Yes.

189
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:32,600
Fun, stand up.

190
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:38,400
And move the chair away.

191
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,240
And step back a little more.

192
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:50,480
A bit more.

193
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,960
This outfit won't work.

194
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,960
This one?

195
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,120
Yes.

196
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,400
I…

197
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,720
AIOON

198
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,560
I remember you've worn it a lot.

199
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,800
Huh?

200
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:07,160
This one? A lot?

201
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,400
Yes.

202
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:12,200
Why don't you change?

203
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,240
Okay.

204
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,240
This outfit doesn't work either.

205
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:29,560
Why not?

206
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:33,400
Well, you get cold easily.

207
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:38,400
And the top doesn't match the pants.

208
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,840
- Doesn't match?
- Yeah.

209
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:48,920
How about you show me your wardrobe?

210
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,360
I'll pick for you.

211
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:52,920
Okay.

212
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:08,120
Closer.

213
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:12,720
That one, the third one.

214
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,160
This one?

215
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,360
No, not that.

216
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,280
How about this one?

217
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:27,080
Put it back. No.

218
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:31,800
I think you should check another wardrobe.

219
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,360
Just go one by one.

220
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,680
One by one.

221
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,440
Yeah.

222
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:46,360
- This one?
- Yes.

223
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,560
This one?

224
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:50,560
Yes.

225
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:53,520
That one's perfect.

226
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:56,680
Okay.

227
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,040
Zip it up.

228
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:07,280
Okay, perfect.

229
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,720
Oon,

230
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:12,720
I feel like it doesn't match at all.

231
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,119
The shirt and the pants don't match.

232
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,920
No, I think

233
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,040
this is the new trend.

234
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,119
I don't think so.

235
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:30,560
Do I really not have anything to wear?

236
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:33,440
It's so hard to choose.

237
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:40,560
Maybe you should let me buy new clothes.

238
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,400
Huh?

239
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:47,320
Okay, you can buy new ones.

240
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,840
How many?

241
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,720
You've rejected

242
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,640
quite a few already.

243
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:56,400
Not including those
you said I've worn too often.

244
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:59,840
As many as you want.

245
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,760
Thank you. I'll go change again.

246
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,560
I'm sure you'll definitely like it.

247
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:11,440
How is it? Do you like it?

248
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:14,920
Fully covered.

249
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,560
Okay.

250
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:20,080
Don't forget what you said.

251
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:22,920
As many new clothes as I want.

252
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:28,960
- Yes.
- Oon, I'll go now. I'm running late.

253
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:35,840
New collection.

254
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,280
As many as you want…

255
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,520
DELIVERY PARKING AREA

256
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,960
Excuse me, can I park here?

257
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,520
I'm dining at the restaurant.

258
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,800
This is a delivery spot,

259
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:09,600
but there are no deliveries right now.
You can park here.

260
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:12,040
Thank you.
Please let me know if I need to move it.

261
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,320
- Sure.
- Thank you.

262
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,240
Please come in.

263
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,000
This way, please.

264
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,880
Here, let me carry that.

265
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,400
It's okay, I've got it.

266
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:42,840
Wait.

267
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:46,520
Can we talk first?
The client isn't here yet.

268
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,400
What is it?

269
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,800
You're really hardworking.

270
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,600
Beautiful and efficient too.

271
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:57,680
If I introduce more clients,
you'd take them, right?

272
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:01,320
Of course. I always give my all at work.

273
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:06,480
Actually, I don't want you to work hard.
I want you to live more comfortably.

274
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,080
I know you're married.

275
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:16,800
I'm just offering you a good option,

276
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:18,480
a life where you don't have to struggle.

277
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,160
A house, a car,

278
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:24,640
anything you want, I can give it to you.

279
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,480
You don't have to leave Aioon,

280
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:31,240
but when I call,

281
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,000
you come.

282
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,800
I already know how you feel about me.

283
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:50,120
Let me be clear. There's no way
anything will ever happen between us.

284
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,720
If it was meant to happen,
it wouldn't have taken this long.

285
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:56,840
I've never thought of you that way,
and I never will.

286
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:04,720
I'll finish this project,
so it doesn't affect my company.

287
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,080
But if you keep thinking like this,

288
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,880
this will be the last project
I ever do with you.

289
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,560
You're going to regret this.

290
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:26,240
Then I'll go with this fabric shade,

291
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,360
so it matches the tile you selected.

292
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,280
That works. The color is nice.

293
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:32,320
Alright.

294
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:38,840
And for the counter and wall tones,

295
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,840
I suggest

296
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:44,680
these two shades, so everything matches
and has the same mood and tone.

297
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:46,480
Light tones are nice. They look clean.

298
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:48,360
Excuse me, ma'am.

299
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:51,960
Could you move your car?
A delivery truck just arrived.

300
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:54,240
Oh, can I have a moment?

301
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,560
I'll move it for you.

302
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,640
Please continue your meeting.

303
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,280
Would you like the clients to wait?

304
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,200
Thank you.

305
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:25,800
Where were we?

306
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:29,920
For the wall and counter tones,

307
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,840
we'll follow this mood and tone.

308
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:34,720
Just like the reference.

309
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:36,720
This way, please.

310
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,760
This way, please.

311
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:21,400
- You can just send me off here.
- Sure.

312
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,480
Goodbye.

313
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,280
Thank you.

314
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,280
Fun.

315
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,240
Fun.

316
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:36,920
I'm sorry.

317
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:40,120
I just wanted you to know how I feel.

318
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,240
I didn't have a choice
since you're married.

319
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,440
But now I understand.

320
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:51,760
I'll go back to being your good friend.

321
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,840
Okay. I hope you can do as you say.

322
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:28,840
Oon-Oon.

323
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,120
You're home late.

324
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,400
Have you eaten?

325
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:42,680
Yes. Alone.

326
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,920
But I bought something for you.
Want me to heat it up?

327
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,040
It's okay.

328
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:57,800
Nice outfit.

329
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:04,080
I'll go shower first.

330
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:48,840
Oon-Oon! Come upstairs now! Right now!

331
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,120
What? Fun?

332
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:25,600
You're not mad anymore?

333
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:29,280
No. Not anymore.

334
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:31,480
Not jealous anymore?

335
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,560
Still jealous.

336
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:42,160
Thank you for making me feel valued.

337
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:06,360
KRIT (OLD FRIEND)

338
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:13,320
Aren't you going to answer?
What if it's important?

339
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:19,120
No. You're more important.

340
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,240
MS. WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

341
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,360
MS. WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

342
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:19,120
MS. PAFUN SETTANUN

343
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,320
Yes, Mr. Krit?

344
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,800
Get me the contact
for that paint company from last week.

345
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:37,880
Which one, sir?

346
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,960
That's your job to find out.
The one that just came recently.

347
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,600
Go find it!

348
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,520
Yes, sir.

349
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,680
Hello, Ms. Boom.

350
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:13,040
Oh.

351
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,920
Hello, Ms. Wirinya.
Do you have a site visit today?

352
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:24,640
Let me check if the foreman is back
from lunch. Please have a seat.

353
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,040
Thank you.

354
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:39,320
INVOICE

355
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,960
- Hello, Ms. Wirinya.
- Hello.

356
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,320
Here to check the site?

357
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:35,640
Please.

358
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,920
Have you looked into hospitals yet?

359
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:51,760
If not, want to use the one I found?

360
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:53,440
- Here.
- Sure.

361
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:58,360
This one has lots of good reviews,
skilled doctors

362
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:00,640
and it's close to our house.

363
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:02,240
Oh, really?

364
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:05,680
Look, reviews from moms.

365
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:06,800
Yeah.

366
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,400
I'm home.

367
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,800
What are you two up to?

368
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:13,160
We're looking for a maternity hospital.

369
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:19,480
So, how do you want to give birth?

370
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:23,000
Naturally.

371
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:24,880
Good.

372
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:29,440
So, are you okay with this place?

373
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:32,960
Yeah, I actually had this one in mind too.

374
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,760
Then I'll take you there myself.

375
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,840
Look. I'll show you that
there are a lot of skilled doctors.

376
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:43,040
Here.

377
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:44,680
Look at this one.

378
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:45,840
Fun.

379
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:49,600
What kind of person is Mr. Kritsana?

380
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,640
Well…

381
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:58,800
Back then, he was fine.
But now, I'm not so sure.

382
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:02,440
From working with him,
I don't think he's that great.

383
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:07,160
Not great? In what way?

384
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:12,840
Work-wise, he's okay.
But personally, he's not.

385
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:15,840
He's

386
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:20,280
extremely confident. Way too confident.
It's uncomfortable being around him.

387
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:28,520
Why? Did he do anything to you?

388
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:31,440
No, not yet.

389
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:36,120
Why'd you ask it like that?
Has he done something to you?

390
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,000
Well,

391
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,640
just a little.

392
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:43,040
But I can handle it.

393
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:45,960
After this project,
I won't work with him again.

394
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,640
What did he do?

395
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:53,360
Well,

396
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,680
he just said some inappropriate things.

397
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,920
Is he the guy you told me about?

398
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:04,760
The childhood friend
who's now your client,

399
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,120
right?

400
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,240
Yeah.

401
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,639
That guy?

402
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:11,480
If I see him…

403
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:16,600
Don't get mad, Mommy.

404
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:20,199
If you hate someone,
your baby might end up looking like them.

405
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:24,400
Oh, right. I forgot.

406
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:26,440
Okay, let's try again.

407
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:29,239
I love him.

408
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,159
What?

409
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:31,080
Hey.

410
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:33,560
I love him so much.

411
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:34,480
Ouch!

412
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,159
- What?
- What happened?

413
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:37,440
- What happened?
- What's wrong?

414
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,320
The baby kicked.

415
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,080
Huh?

416
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:43,159
Can I feel?

417
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:46,000
Where? Can I feel?

418
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,480
Where?

419
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:49,960
I want to feel it too.

420
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,760
Fun.

421
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,639
Share her with me too.

422
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,800
Where?

423
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,400
I can't feel anything.

424
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:03,680
- Where? Did you feel anything?
- Where?

425
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:04,880
I can't feel anything.

426
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,240
Oh.

427
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,720
- Did you feel it?
- No.

428
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,200
Where is it?

429
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:14,960
- Do you feel it?
- No.

430
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:25,520
The heartbeat is strong.

431
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:28,680
Overall growth looks good,

432
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:32,240
and today's ultrasound
is within the normal range.

433
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:35,880
So today, you pass.

434
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:55,000
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

435
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:58,440
What money is this?

436
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:00,520
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

437
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,280
Hey, Oon, come take a look at this.

438
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:06,000
Okay.

439
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:11,560
Can we remove this beam?

440
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:13,880
It'd look better without it.

441
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:17,120
Then why didn't you design it better
in the first place?

442
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,360
So you wouldn't be out of work.
Come on, help me out.

443
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:23,720
Fine, let's do it.

444
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:24,720
Alright.

445
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,360
Here.

446
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,560
Oh.

447
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,400
Are you out jogging?

448
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:43,840
- Hello.
- Hi.

449
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:47,640
I'm just getting some fresh air
and doing some light exercise.

450
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:49,160
I see.

451
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:55,440
What's wrong? Feeling bloated?

452
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:58,640
You don't exercise enough.

453
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:00,640
Actually…

454
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,720
I'm pregnant.

455
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:12,720
Please don't mind me asking.

456
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:16,520
I've never seen the baby's father.
Where is he?

457
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:20,160
Well…

458
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:27,280
Hearing your story,
I can tell you're so strong.

459
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:29,280
But it's fine.

460
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,320
Women these days can do anything.

461
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:37,960
If you ever have a problem,
you can always talk to me. Okay?

462
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,320
Thank you.

463
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:53,520
Do you have any protective charms
for you and the baby yet?

464
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:33,680
Aunt Wee, I'll return this for now.

465
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,840
If I need it later, I'll come ask again.

466
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:38,880
Oh, no need to return it.
Keep it. It brings good luck.

467
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:41,560
It's okay. You keep it. Thank you.

468
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:44,760
Then do this.
If you ever need one, tell me.

469
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:48,880
I have many, for all kinds of luck. Look.

470
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:52,560
Here.

471
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:56,480
Anyway, let's keep in touch.

472
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:57,840
Okay, see you.

473
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:00,000
See you.

474
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:07,600
Aioon,

475
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:11,840
why did you design this beam so big?
And there are too many columns.

476
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:15,480
Did you even check if your design
is structurally possible?

477
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:18,200
Without these columns,
how would it support the structure?

478
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:21,680
But it's design. Design, you know?

479
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:22,840
- And you--
- Stop.

480
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:26,640
Yes?

481
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:27,800
Ms. Wirinya.

482
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:29,880
Come to the meeting room now.

483
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:32,120
Yes.

484
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:37,880
Nu just called me in.

485
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,880
But something feels off.

486
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:47,960
It's Nu.

487
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,200
Yes, Nu?

488
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:53,680
Mr. Thanwa, come to the meeting room.

489
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,200
Yes.

490
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:01,840
My call was weird too.
He even used my full name.

491
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:07,720
What does this mean?

492
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:10,760
Can either of you explain?

493
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:29,760
WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

494
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,280
30,000 BAHT

495
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:42,200
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

496
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,680
What money is this?

497
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,960
Nu, I don't know anything about this.

498
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:56,000
With evidence this clear,
how can you deny it?

499
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:03,920
Did you two really collude
over this amount of money?

500
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:07,600
No, Nu.

501
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:12,120
Mr. Kritsana was the one who told me
to add that company to the vendor list.

502
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:15,600
Where's the memo? The memo?!

503
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:24,480
- This is it, right?
- Yeah. Okay.

504
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:33,400
Hello, Mr. Kritsana.

505
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:35,440
Mr. Thanwa.

506
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:39,240
Please add the Tough Paint company
to the vendor list.

507
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:42,560
I'll send the memo later. It's urgent.

508
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,880
Got it.

509
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,560
Nu.

510
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:54,000
You know us.

511
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:01,640
And so what?

512
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:03,960
The evidence is clear.

513
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:12,840
Please give us time to prove it.

514
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,840
You have four days.

515
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:23,400
Find proof.

516
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:29,480
Otherwise, you're both terminated.

517
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:32,440
Understood?

518
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:35,360
- Yes.
- Yes.

519
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:38,040
You're suspended starting today.

520
00:42:39,640 --> 00:42:43,640
Can I take photos of these documents?

521
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:08,800
What's wrong with her?

522
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:15,880
Morning sickness. She felt dizzy.

523
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:18,080
She took some medicine and fell asleep.

524
00:43:20,920 --> 00:43:23,440
There's rad na. You want to eat?

525
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:26,440
Not yet.

526
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:30,080
I'm not really hungry. I'm tired.

527
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:33,720
I'll go shower first.

528
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:14,240
Oon, what's wrong? You can tell me.

529
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:20,680
It's nothing.

530
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:34,200
Are you okay?

531
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:47,840
Fun…

532
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:51,000
I…

533
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:57,240
I can't build a future for you anymore.

534
00:44:59,480 --> 00:45:01,800
I've been suspended from work.

535
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:06,200
Nu accused me of embezzlement,

536
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,880
but I didn't do it.

537
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:11,320
I didn't.

538
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:17,160
Now I can't earn money.
I can't take care of you.

539
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:19,880
I have nothing left.

540
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:24,800
I can't do this anymore. I can't. I can't.

541
00:45:26,560 --> 00:45:27,920
I can't do it.

542
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:34,640
Oon.

543
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:39,920
It's okay. It's okay.

544
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:43,440
I can take care of you.

545
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:51,800
We've been through so much together.

546
00:45:52,480 --> 00:45:54,320
We've faced worse than this.

547
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,680
We started from nothing before.

548
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:02,040
If we have to start from zero again,
that's okay.

549
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:12,200
It's not a big deal. We'll get through it.

550
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:16,040
I'm hardworking, you know.

551
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:18,920
I can take care of you.

552
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:34,880
I'm sorry, Fun. I'm sorry.

553
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:45,320
It's okay.

554
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:48,200
I love you.

555
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,160
Thank you.

556
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:06,000
I'm sorry.

557
00:47:42,600 --> 00:47:47,080
About your old offer…
I wonder if you still remember it.

558
00:47:47,160 --> 00:47:49,320
In the end, you chose me.

559
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:52,560
Once we finish tonight,
you can get your new car tomorrow.

560
00:47:54,560 --> 00:47:56,160
Let me see.

561
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:38,040
